  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="View of Tuscany landscape and poppiest" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">Get to know the Tuscany’s highlights on this fantastic tour. From wine tasting in Chianti to exploring Florence and Siena with a local expert, this guided tour will take you to the heart of the region. <br /></span></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 1 </span><br />Fly into Pisa where your transfer will be waiting to take you to your hotel in Montecatini Terme. You’ll have time to unpack before meeting the group and tour manager over a welcome drink before dinner.</p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 2 <br /></span>When people think of <a data-udi="umb://document/58d85ec0faa548b2ab580143fdc9b722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/58d85ec0faa548b2ab580143fdc9b722}" title="Tuscany &amp; Umbria">Tuscany</a> it’s the Chianti wine region that first comes to mind. Winding country roads weave through rolling vineyards with medieval hilltop towns in the background. Today, you’ll enjoy exploring this beautiful area with a stop to taste some of the famous labels that it produces.</p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 3 <br /></span><span>No visit to Tuscany would be complete without a stop in the region’s capital, <a data-udi="umb://document/8b79e45930f145f6b156a9152415fa9b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8b79e45930f145f6b156a9152415fa9b}" title="Florence">Florence</a>. The city is bursting with Renaissance artwork, stunning architecture and beautiful scenery. You’ll get to visit the Ufizzi Gallery with an expert guide to walk you round and stop at Brunelleschi’s Dome. You’ll also get some free time to explore the city at your own pace.</span><br /><span><br /><img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="View of the Leaning Tower of Pisa" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /><br /></span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 4 <br /></span><span>After a busy start to the trip, today is at leisure to enjoy Montecatini. Perhaps take the funicular up to Montecatini Alto to admire the views or take a treatment at one of the resort's spas.</span></p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 5 <br /></span>Today is a guided tour of <a data-udi="umb://document/8502468fe6eb499faab16739425f51ec" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8502468fe6eb499faab16739425f51ec}" title="Siena &amp; Chianti">Siena</a>, visiting its beautiful Gothic cathedral before heading to the medieval town of <a data-udi="umb://document/3636c17f7e9f439bb5a34f8cb2e9ced3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3636c17f7e9f439bb5a34f8cb2e9ced3}" title="San Gimignano">San Gimignano</a>, famous for its towers that dominate the skyline.</span></p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 6<br /></span></span>A day at leisure or perhaps take the local train to the pretty, walled town of Lucca. A little further down the line is Pisa and the famous leaning tower.</p>
<span> <img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="view of the bell tower in Lucca" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /></span><a data-udi="umb://document/61b9b813ca6d419794fd819362771320" href="/{localLink:umb://document/61b9b813ca6d419794fd819362771320}" title="Where to go cycling on an e-bike"><br /></a>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 7<br /></span></span><span>A day at leisure.</span></p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 8<br /></span></span>Transfer back to Pisa airport for your return flight to UK.</p>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Tour Includes<br /><br /></h2>
<p>7 nights half board accommodation at the <a data-udi="umb://document/074ee7813ef64428b3982b31d9f31c38" href="/{localLink:umb://document/074ee7813ef64428b3982b31d9f31c38}" title="Treasures of Tuscany Tour">4* Hotel Ariston in Montecatini</a></p>
<p>Expertly-guided tours of Florence and Siena</p>
<p>A visit to Chianti with wine tasting</p>
<p>Free time to enjoy the spas of Montecatini Terme</p>
<p>An experienced Tour Manager throughout your tour </p>
<p>Return flights and overseas transfers </p>
<p>14 meals: 7 breakfasts &amp; 7 dinners </p>
<p> </p>
</div>
